p style="text-align:center" <b>APPENDIX A</b>

p style="text-align:center" <b>Registering in Certify</b>

p
  'To create your account, visit
  a>href='certify.SBA.gov' certify.SBA.gov
  | and click on the "Create an Account" button. Create your password based on the requirements listed on screen in Certify during registration; the password is complex to protect your personal information captured in Certify. <b>Note: The initial account creation should be completed by the firm's owner upon whom 8(a) certification was based. <i>This is not applicable to entity-owned firms.</i></b>

p
  'As part of registration, you will receive an email from
  a> href='mailto:certify@sba.gov' certify@sba.gov
  ' to verify your email address.  Click the confirmation link in the email; you will be taken to
  a> href='certify.SBA.gov' certify.SBA.gov
  ' to log in with your credentials (i.e. email and password).  If you do not receive the registration email from Certify after you have created your account, check your spam folder and add
  a> href='mailto:certify@sba.gov' certify@sba.gov
  ' to your contacts.  <b>Please note that the confirmation link will expire after 24 hours</b>.

p
  ' The first time you log in, you will need to link your firm's
  a> href="https://www.SAM.gov" SAM.gov
  ' profile to the
  a> href='certify.SBA.gov' certify.SBA.gov
  ' system using your firm's DUNS number, TIN number, EIN or SSN, and MPIN (created in
  a> href="https://www.SAM.gov" SAM.gov
  '). Follow the prompts to review data pulled from
  a> href="https://www.SAM.gov" SAM.gov
  ' and connect your firm to your
  a> href='certify.SBA.gov' certify.SBA.gov
  ' account. If your SAM account is inactive, you will need to go into SAM.gov prior to registering in Certify. This process can take more than one day.

p
  'If additional assistance is needed, please contact the
  a> href='/help' Certify Help Desk
  ' and include your DUNS number along with a description and any relevant screenshots to help identify and resolve the issue.